  },
  {
    "slide": 32,
    "title": "",
    "texts": [
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Effect of NOISE: What is to be done?\u000bCourtesy Juan Carlos Niebles and Ranjay Krishna"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Smoothing the image should help, by forcing pixels different to their neighbors (=noise pixels?) to look more like neighbors."
      }
    ],
    "has_images": false,
    "image_files": []
  },
  {
    "slide": 33,
    "title": "",
    "texts": [
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Smoothing with different filters\u000bCourtesy Juan Carlos Niebles and Ranjay Krishna"
      }
    ],
    "has_images": true,
    "image_files": [
      "/home/rishabh/Documents/IITM/CV/Notes/MD/Images/extracted/Edge detection/slide_33_img_2.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "slide": 34,
    "title": "",
    "texts": [
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Solution: smooth first \u000bCourtesy Juan Carlos Niebles and Ranjay Krishna"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Image -> Smoothen the image -> Take the derivative to detect Edges"
      }
    ],
    "has_images": true,
    "image_files": [
      "/home/rishabh/Documents/IITM/CV/Notes/MD/Images/extracted/Edge detection/slide_34_img_2.png"
    ]
  },
  {
    "slide": 35,
    "title": "",
    "texts": [
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Derivative theorem of convolution - This saves us one operation \u000bCourtesy Juan Carlos Niebles and Ranjay Krishna"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Image -> Smoothen the image -> Take the derivative to detect Edges"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "These two steps can be combined."
