  {
    "slide": 70,
    "title": "",
    "texts": [
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "Canny Edge Detector: Double thresholding using Hysteresis thresholding\u000bCourtesy : Bernd Girod;  Juan Carlos Niebles and Ranjay Krishna"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "If the gradient M[x,y] at a pixel is"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "above \u03b8High, declare it as an \u2018strong edge pixel\u2019"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "below \u03b8Low, declare it as a \u201cnon-edge-pixel\u201d"
      },
      {
        "level": 0,
        "text": "between \u03b8Low and \u03b8High \u2013 Consider its neighbors iteratively then declare it an \u201cedge pixel\u201d if it is connected to an \u2018strong edge pixel\u2019 directly or via pixels between Low and High."
      }
    ],
